Mercy Akide-Udoh has been named Regent University Athletic Department’s Coach of the Year, reports Ayo Bada. The Nigerian, who has only just completed her first season as Head Coach of the University’s Women’s Soccer programme, was a unanimous choice for the award, voted for by all the coaches in the Virginia Beach-based University. In her first season, Akide-Udoh took the team from zero wins in their first season, to five wins. Responding, the former Super Falcons of Nigeria captain was full appreciation to all and expressed her happiness in winning the award. “This is such an unexpected honour for me,” said Akide-Udoh as she received her award. “I will like to thank everyone who voted and also thank my players who have made such an enjoyable time for me here.”